* Forms
** Disable trace?
** Documentation
*** Extra fields in printfield etc?
*** No form/lang for verbatim, special fields etc. only lists, names and field types
** fields need two optional arguments for form and lang in bbl, by default empty for backwards compat
** Potential issues
*** You can sort on one form of a name/title but labelname/labeltitle could cause labels to be generated from another form? One way to avoid is to specify a labelname form and then to sort on labelname?

These need extra args everywhere and they are called by other things which
need extra args

abx@field <- dealing with this
abx@list
abx@name








saveentry and reencode need to know about possible forms and langs for fields so it can iterate over them to save or delete them.

Search for any of the below changed macros and see if their calls need editing

\blx@getformat needs to be form/lang enabled
\Declare*Format needs to be form/lang enabled


\field -> \blx@bbl@fielddef -> \blx@bbl@addfield -> abx@field
\list  -> \blx@bbl@listdef  -> -> abx@list
\name  -> \blx@bbl@namedef  -> -> abx@name


\def\do##1{%
  \def\do####1{%
    \def\do######1{%
      \cslet{abx@field@##1@####1@######1}\relax}%
    \dolistcsloop{abx@scripts@field@lang}}%
  \dolistcsloop{abx@scripts@field@form}}%

\listgadd{\abx@scripts@field,list,name@form}{#1}%
\listgadd{\abx@scripts@field,list,name@lang}{#2}%



